               <msContents>
                  <summary>Papyrus memorandum from Ptolemaios to Nechoutes(?) in the Arsinoites (modern name: Fayyum), Egypt, ordering him to assist three cavalry soldiers, Andromachos, Aristaios, and Paraibatos the sons of Andromachos, in the measurement of their land. These three men have been given 80 arouras of land each, and Petobastis informs them of the exploitation of their land near Eleusis and Tebetnou. Dated to Phaophi 29, year 2 (Dec. 4, 180 B.C. or Dec. 1, 169 B.C.)</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 32.8 x 12.6 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">27 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers on the recto; written along the fibers on the verso</note>
                     <note type="general">Upper margin of 4.5 cm.; lower margin of 1 cm.; left margin of 3 cm.; small right margin</note>
                     <note type="general">Extracted from mummy cartonnage with P.Duk.inv. 313-317 and P.Duk.inv. 319-323</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv 318 was formerly P.Duk.inv. MF84 6</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
